The paper addresses the problem of robot movement adaptation for manipulation tasks, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The proposed framework involves learning from demonstrations and human-in-the-loop interactions, which suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The framework also considers user feedback, indicating the importance of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the experiments involve a humanoid platform, which suggests the involvement of computer vision (cs.CV) techniques for perception and sensing.
